Generic single-database configuration.

Local dev:

Make changes to models (models.py)
Restart the backend
    (docker compose down backend)
    (docker compose up backend --build -d)
Open a shell into to the backend container
    (docker compose exec backend bash)
Create an alembic revision
    (alembic revision --autogenerate -m "what the revision wants to do"
Review that revision!
    /app/app/alembic/versions (note: there will be a nested app directory in docker container and you will start in the higher level app)
Once you are satisfied with the revision!
Run the migration
    alembic upgrade head

Now you absolutely need to:
    move the file you've created through alembic autogenerate into your alembic/versions folder locally, with the same name.
    check it in!
